**A debounce function limits how often a given function can be called, ensuring it's only invoked after a specified pause in activity.**

```javascript
// Debounce function
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example usage:
window.addEventListener('resize', debounce(() => {
  console.log('Window resized!');
}, 300));
```
*In this example, "Window resized!" will only log once the user stops resizing the window for at least 300 milliseconds.*
